    "comment": "Rationale: Authors use a FRET sensor of ERK1/2 activation localized to presynapses and correlate the presence of over-expressed SIPA1L2 with lower fluorescence lifetime of the donor pair, that indirectly indicated ERK activation.\nIn a rescue experiments, restoration of SIPA1L2 rescues the ERK-dependent phosphorylation of Synapsin in sipa1l2-/- cells.. Experimental description: Recombinant DNA used to visualized SIPA1L2 tagged with fluorescent reporters derives from mouse (Suppl. table 1). Recombinant DNA was over expressed in rat hippocampal primary neurons and wt and sipa1l2-/- primary hippocampal neurons.",
